detaileddescription.para: macro used to represent success of library variable to check initialization status

briefdescription.para: Function to initialize bmm150.This needs to be called before calling any other API.

parameterdescription.para: when any of the input parameter(bmm150Info or bmm150Info->ISRCallback) is NULL.
when any of the input parameter for BST library API is NULL.
when error is returned from BST library API.

simplesect.para: In case of other failures refer BSP_SensorNode_Enable or #I2CSensorTransceiver_Init API's.
1) The return value consist of (First MSB Byte represents Package ID,Next Byte represents Severity and Last 2LSB Bytes represents error code).
2) The support of multiple instances is not possible due to the limitation in the BST library.
3) Calling Bmm150 initialization API present in sensorUtils (Bmm150Utils_initialize) and BST library (bmm050_init) concurrently will lead to unexpected behaviour.
